Researched different development tools suitable for creating our phising awareness game
Compared HTML/CSS/JavaScript, Canvas, and Scratch based on their strengths and limitations and whether they are suitable for our target audience.
Evaluated the strengths of each tool, including ease of use, interactivity, and visual graphic capabilities.
Analysed the limitations of each tool, such as complexity, lack of advanced features, or development time
Considered among three on which tool would best support phishing simulations and realistic webpage design
Evaluated which tool could provide clear feedback systems such as animations, scores, and pop-ups
Evaluated which tool was easiest for the group to learn today
Determined which tool is suitable to complete project within the time we have
Also compared which tools would provide professional coding evidence for GitHub uploads
In the end concluded that HTML/CSS/JavaScript was the best overall option for the project because it is practical, realistic, and suitable for the audience
But also Justified why  Scratch is less suitable compared to HTML for implementation in project.
